{
  "texts": [
    "The initial learning rate is set to 0.001 and we use a batch size of 1 to avoid overfitting on the train set.",
    "As mentioned before, truncated backpropagation through time is used as an optimization strategies, with the goal of removing the effects of exploding/vanishing gradients caused by the recurrent component.",
    "Thus, we split the sequence of 30 frames in two equal parts and stop the gradients when passing from one part to the next, as the standard TBPTT is implemented.",
    "Using these settings, the training time for ERVT is 5.4 hours, Lastly, we use a dropout probability of 0.6.",
    "All the experiments are performed on a laptop with Nvidia RTX 3060 6 GB."
  ]
}